The `logtopic` use case as follows:

```
package main

import (
	"github.com/apache/pulsar/pulsar-function-go/log"
	"github.com/apache/pulsar/pulsar-function-go/pf"
)

func hello() {
	log.Info("hello.")
}

func main() {
	pf.Start(hello)
}
```

Two places to note:

-  `pulsar-function-go` depends on `pulsar-client-go` of `cgo` version, so make sure you have successfully built `pulsar-client-cpp` locally.
-  Please make sure your go version is greater than `go1.11`. 


The problem with your above is that you are manipulating the `go mod` error, you can re-import the project, and run `go mod download`.

Specific issues can be viewed: [cmd/go: 'cannot find module for path' when importing from subdirectories
](https://github.com/golang/go/issues/26645)

The general reason is because you have problems executing `go mod init`

